data.title: Dean's List
data.text:
At the end of each semester, recognition of the Dean’s List of students for distinguished academic achievement is awarded to students who achieve a minimum QPA of at least 3.5—for the term, provided that, in that term they have successfully completed courses totaling a minimum of 12 credits to a degree. The Office of the Dean of Undergraduate Studies recognizes students in the first-year class with a letter of commendation. Dean’s List recognition for all other undergraduate students is coordinated through Loyola College of Arts and Science, the Sellinger of School of Business or the School of Education (depending on the student’s undergraduate major).

The following members of the Class of 2027 have earned Dean’s List honors for the Fall 2024 semester:
